    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1977-11-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1977-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="121"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                <head>121. Letter From President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> to
                    General Torrijos<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d121fn1">Source: Carter
                        Library, White House Central Files, Subject File, FO 3–1, Panama Canal, 1.
                        No classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1977-11-28">November 28, 1977</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear General <persName corresp="#p_THO_1">Torrijos</persName>:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>You will recall that when you visited Washington on October 14, you and I agreed
                    on a Statement of Understanding which was made public at the White House in
                    Washington on October 14.<note n="2" xml:id="d121fn2">See <ref target="#d113"
                            >Document 113</ref>.</note> A copy is enclosed.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d121fn3">Attached but not printed. See <ref target="#d106fn8"
                            >footnote 8, Document 106</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I wish to confirm that the United States Government considers the Statement of
                    Understanding to be the authoritative interpretation of the relevant provisions
                    of the Treaty Concerning the Permanent Neutrality and Operation of the Panama
                    Canal, signed on September 7, 1977.</p>
                <pb facs="0373" n="338" xml:id="pg_338"/>
                <p>I would be grateful if you would confirm that the Government of Panama likewise
                    considers the Statement of Understanding to be the authoritative interpretation
                    of the relevant provisions of the Neutrality Treaty.</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Jimmy Carter</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
